  <caaml:metaData>
    <caaml:comment>- Simple test pit, just to check out what will become the base layer for this year's snowpack&#13;
- South facing slopes had numerous sluff/point release avalanches that released down to the bed surface; this is due to recent warm temps and no new snow in two weeks&#13;
- North facing slopes are healthy but have a surface hoar layer on top that varied from large crystals in treed areas to smaller .1 size crystals at higher elevations (above 1700m)</caaml:comment>
